{"event":{"data":{"goals":[],"history":[{"_id":"69e888086d7bd74f42a375f5","content":"how do i meditate","role":"user","timestamp":"2026-04-22T08:34:16.977Z"},{"_id":"69e888086d7bd74f42a375f6","content":"It is wonderful that you are curious about meditation. Taking the initiative to explore new tools for self-regulation is a significant step toward improving your mental well-being. Meditation is a practice of training your attention and awareness, and it can be a very grounding way to manage stress.\n\nFor a beginner, I recommend starting with a simple **Mindfulness Meditation** focused on the breath. Here is a basic way to begin:\n\n1.  **Find a Quiet Space:** Sit or lie down in a comfortable position where you won’t be interrupted for a few minutes.\n2.  **Settle In:** Close your eyes or soften your gaze. Notice the weight of your body against the chair or floor.\n3.  **Focus on the Breath:** Bring your attention to the physical sensation of breathing. Notice the air entering your nose, the rise and fall of your chest, or the expansion of your belly. You don’t need to change your breath; just observe it.\n4.  **Acknowledge Distractions:** Your mind will naturally wander—this is completely normal. When you notice a thought, feeling, or sound, simply acknowledge it without judgment and gently guide your focus back to your breath.\n5.  **Be Kind to Yourself:** There is no \"perfect\" way to meditate. The goal isn't to clear your mind entirely, but to notice when it has wandered and practice returning to the present moment.\n\nYou might try doing this for just 3 to 5 minutes today. How does the idea of trying a short practice like that feel to you?","metadata":{"analysis":{"emotionalState":"Curious/Neutral","progressIndicators":["Proactive seeking of coping tools","Engagement in self-improvement"],"recommendedApproach":"Provide foundational instruction on mindfulness meditation, focusing on simple breath-work and observation techniques.","riskLevel":0,"themes":["Mindfulness","Meditation techniques","Self-regulation"]},"progress":{"emotionalState":"Curious/Neutral","riskLevel":0}},"role":"assistant","timestamp":"2026-04-22T08:34:16.981Z"}],"memory":{"sessionContext":{"conversationThemes":[],"currentTechnique":null},"userProfile":{"emotionalState":[],"preferences":{},"riskLevel":0}},"message":"explain more about Acknowledge Distractions","systemPrompt":"You are an AI therapist assistant. Your role is to:\n        1. Provide empathetic and supportive responses\n        2. Use evidence-based therapeutic techniques\n        3. Maintain professional boundaries\n        4. Monitor for risk factors\n        5. Guide users toward their therapeutic goals"},"name":"therapy/session.message"},"level":"info","message":"Sending message to Inngest:","timestamp":"2026-04-22T08:35:58.149Z"}
